== Duties and History under the Ritsuryo System ==
The Shoryoryo was initially established as {{ill|Shoryoshi|ja|諸陵司|12=draft}} (和訓: みささぎのつかさ) under the {{ill|Ritsuryo Code|ja|律令|12=draft}}. In {{ill|729|ja|729th year|12=draft}} ({{ill|Shinki|ja|神亀|12=draft}} 6/ {{ill|Tenpyo|ja|天平|12=draft}} 元年), it was elevated to the status of a {{ill|ryo|ja|寮|12=draft}}. Its primary duties included managing {{ill|Imperial tombs|ja|陵墓|1=Japanese imperial tombs|lt=Imperial tomb|12=draft}}, conducting {{ill|funeral rites|ja|喪葬|12=draft}}, and overseeing rituals for the funerals of members of the {{ill|Imperial Family|ja|皇族|12=draft}}. Specifically, it managed the registries of the {{ill|Ryoho|ja|陵戸|12=draft}}, who were assigned to guard the tombs. In cases of misfortune, officials were sometimes sent to console the spirits of neglected Imperial Family members, as seen in the case of {{ill|Prince Sawara|ja|早良親王|12=draft}}.

