'''Shoryoryo''' (諸陵寮) was a [[:en:Ritsuryō|government office]] under the [[:en:Ministry of Ceremonies (Japan)|Ministry of Ceremonial Affairs]] during the [[:en:Ritsuryō|Ritsuryo system]] in Japan. It was briefly revived in the early years of the Meiji government, abolished once, and later re-established with modifications in [[:en:1886|1886]]. Its successor, the [[:en:Archives and Mausolea Department|Archives and Mausolea Department]], currently manages imperial tombs ([[:en:Japanese imperial tombs|Japanese imperial tombs]]).

== Duties and History under the Ritsuryo System ==
The Shoryoryo was initially established as {{ill|Shoryoshi|ja|諸陵司|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shoryoshi|qq=}} (和訓: みささぎのつかさ) under the [[:en:Traditional Chinese law|Ritsuryo Code]]. In [[:en:729|729]] ([[:en:Jinki (era)|Shinki]] 6/ [[:en:Tenpyō|Tenpyo]] 元年), it was elevated to the status of a [[:en:Dormitory|ryo]]. Its primary duties included managing {{ill|Imperial tombs|ja|陵墓|1=Japanese imperial tombs|lt=Imperial tomb|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial tombs|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese imperial tombs|qq=}}, conducting {{ill|funeral rites|ja|喪葬|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/funeral rites|qq=}}, and overseeing rituals for the funerals of members of the {{ill|Imperial Family|ja|皇族|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial Family|qq=}}. Specifically, it managed the registries of the {{ill|Ryoho|ja|陵戸|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ryoho|qq=}}, who were assigned to guard the tombs. In cases of misfortune, officials were sometimes sent to console the spirits of neglected Imperial Family members, as seen in the case of [[:en:Prince Sawara|Prince Sawara]].

== Staff ==
* [[:en:Head|Head (従五位上)]]
* {{ill|Assistant (正六位下)|ja|助|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Assistant (正六位下)|qq=}}
* {{ill|Junior Assistant (正七位下)|ja|允|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Assistant (正七位下)|qq=}}
* {{ill|Clerk (従七位上)|ja|属|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Clerk (従七位上)|qq=}}

* {{ill|Shisho|ja|史生|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shisho|qq=}}
* {{ill|Shibu|ja|使部|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shibu|qq=}}
* {{ill|Chokutei|ja|直丁|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chokutei|qq=}}

* {{ill|Ryoho|ja|陵戸|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ryoho|qq=}}
* {{ill|Shugo|ja|守戸|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shugo|qq=}}

=== Staff of Shoryoshi ===
* {{ill|Chief (正六位上)|ja|正|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chief (正六位上)|qq=}}
* {{ill|Deputy (従七位下)|ja|佑|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Deputy (従七位下)|qq=}}
* {{ill|Senior Clerk (大初位上)|ja|大令史|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Clerk (大初位上)|qq=}}
* {{ill|Junior Clerk (大初位下)|ja|少令史|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Clerk (大初位下)|qq=}}
* [[:en:Radical 32|Tsubebe]] – Ritual staff for funerals.

== Meiji Government ==
In {{ill|1869|ja|明治2年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1869|qq=}} (Meiji 2), the Shoryoryo was re-established under the [[:en:Department of Divinities|Department of Divinities]] with roles such as head, assistant, clerk, and others. The head of the Shoryoryo at the time was {{ill|Toda Tadazumi|ja|戸田忠至|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toda Tadazumi|qq=}}, who also served as a {{ill|Ministry of the Imperial Household|ja|宮内大丞|Ministry of the Imperial Household=Ministry of the Imperial Household|lt=Miyauchi-daiyoku|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ministry of the Imperial Household|qq=}}.<ref name=ishinshi-5-478>{{cite book|author=文部省維新史料編纂事務局|title=維新史|volume=5|year=1941|pages=478|url={{NDLDC|1242382/260}}}}</ref><ref name="toike">{{cite book|和書|author=外池昇|title=天皇陵の近代史|publisher=吉川弘文館|year=2000|page=71}}</ref> During this time, the tombs of past emperors were re-evaluated, and posthumous titles were granted, such as [[:en:Emperor Kōbun|Emperor Kobun]] and [[:en:Emperor Junnin|Emperor Junnin]].<ref name=ishinshi-5-478/>

In {{ill|1871|ja|明治4年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1871|qq=}}, the Shoryoryo was merged into the [[:en:Ministry of Divinities|Ministry of Divinities]]. After several reorganizations, it was incorporated into the [[:en:Ministry of Religion (Japan)|Ministry of Religion]] as the Shoryo Section. Later, the management was transferred to the [[:en:Ministry of the Imperial Household|Imperial Household Ministry]], where it became the Imperial Tombs Section in 1878.<ref name=toike/>

In {{ill|1886|ja|明治19年|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1886|qq=}}, the Shoryoryo was revived.<ref name=ishinshi-5-478/><ref name=toike/>

